        [
        {I found a pair of shoes.}
{I could leave them in front of me, or I could wear them.}
{I am...}
        ]

        [
        {I am wearing the shoes.}
{It's a comfortable fit around my feet.}
{I feel strange, as if I've gone to a different world.}
{After some time, I notice a sharp axe in front of me.}
{Maybe it was there all along. Maybe I didn't notice it until now.}
{As I move forwards, I know I can have anything I want.}
{But at the same time, a weapon will change everything.}
{I...}
        ]

        [
       {I'm not wearing the shoes.}
{The shoes' crimson color gets deeper.}
        ]

        [
       {I take hold of the axe.}
{This tool can cut through anyone's foot, even one's own.}
{The blade of the axe is as sharp as a razor.}
{I know who sharpened it.}
{The shoes are colorless.}
{They will be red soon.}
        ]

        [
       {I don't take the axe.}
{Only the shoes know the way that I should go.}
        ]

